-- Three Argentine Provinces Preparing $1.5 Billion Bond Sales, Cronista Says
-- Bill Faries
-- 2010-07-27T11:17:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/three-argentine-provinces-preparing-1-5-billion-bond-sales-cronista-says.html

          
          
             Three Argentine provinces are
preparing to sell about $1.5 billion in bonds this year,
newspaper El Cronista said, citing economy ministers from the
provinces.   
 Santa Fe wants to sell 1 billion pesos ($254 million) of
bonds by the end of the year, provincial Economy Minister Angel
Sciara told the Buenos Aires-based daily. Buenos Aires province
and Cordoba province are also considering sales, El Cronista
said.   
          
          


  


        